<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1351,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,822,1495,1522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Justification of the synonymy and updated diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tumbrinck, J. &amp; Skejo, J." box="[835,1139,1495,1522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" pagination="525 - 580" refId="ref5056" refString="Tumbrinck, J. &amp; Skejo, J. (2017) Taxonomic and biogeographic revision of the New Guinean genus Ophiotettix Walker, 1871 (Tetrigidae: Metrodorinae: Ophiotettigini trib. nov.), with the descriptions of 33 new species. Biodiversity, biogeography and nature conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea, 3, 525 - 580, pls. 104 - 124." type="journal article" year="2017">Tumbrinck &amp; Skejo (2017)</bibRefCitation>
reported that genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Threciscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Threciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[280,387,1531,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,387,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Spartolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[500,620,1531,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Threciscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,620,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Threciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacking foliaceous, modified maxillary palpy. This is incorrect and by detailed inspection we observed that all our specimens have foliaceous apical segments of maxillary palpi. Those segments are not as widened as in other species and as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1871" box="[792,918,1603,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Ophiotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[792,918,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Ophiotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are surely widened. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[1198,1436,1603,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugionatus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1436,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Spartolus pugionatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. resurr. is thus put back into the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[648,755,1639,1665]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[648,755,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Spartolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it has less differences from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[1106,1252,1640,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricostatus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1252,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">S. tricostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricostatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">S. tricostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has from 
<emphasis box="[296,526,1675,1702]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[296,396,1676,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minax">S. minax</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[406,526,1675,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Threciscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Threciscus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
syn. nov. is thus synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[931,1038,1675,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[931,1038,1675,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Spartolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[1173,1280,1675,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Spartolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1280,1675,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Spartolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the 
<collectingCountry box="[193,319,1711,1737]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and its members are characterized in (1) narrow scutellum (almost absent), (2) elongated head, (3) colorful appearance with red, yellow and orange colors, (4) absence of wings, (5) presence of widened, foliaceous maxillary palpi and (6) lateral paranotal spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
